Unity Catalog is an open source storage layer which is used to classify and
manage data.

It is mainly used for Data Governance purpose.

It helps us managing a large amount of data while maintaining Data Integrity,reliability and
accuracy.

It helps us in keeping track of multiple workspace and multiple teams data under a single
catalogue.

It provide security features such as permission where we can grant permission to specific
users for specific access such as read ,write or update.

Inside DataBricks we have one option called   Catalogue we have to click on it
then we have a option called + symbol then we have to click on create a Catalogue.

